.SH NAME
gmc-wt-init - Generate shell integration script


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgmc wt init  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate a shell integration script for gmc.

.PP
Add the following to your shell's rc file:

.PP
# For bash (~/.bashrc)
  eval "$(gmc wt init bash)"

.PP
# For zsh (~/.zshrc)
  eval "$(gmc wt init zsh)"

.PP
# For fish (~/.config/fish/config.fish)
  gmc wt init fish | source

.PP
After this, 'gmc wt switch' will be able to change your working directory.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for init


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	Config file (default: $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/gmc/config.yaml)

.PP
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="text"
	Output format: text or json


